# 643. Maximum Average Subarray I
Pattern:
Sliding Window

Window Type:
Fixed Size Window

Template:

low = 0
sum = 0
for(high = 0; high < n; high++){
    sum += nums[high]
    if(high - low + 1 == k){
        maxSum = max(maxSum, sum)
        sum -= nums[low]
        low++
    }
}
average = maxSum / k

Key Idea:
Maintain a window of size K.
Track maximum sum.

Learning:
- Fixed Size Window
- Running Sum
- Maximum Window Tracking

Complexity:
Time: O(n)
Space: O(1)

Code:
class Solution {
    public double findMaxAverage(int[] nums, int k) {

        int low = 0;

        // Current window sum
        long windowSum = 0;

        // Maximum window sum found so far
        long maxSum = Long.MIN_VALUE;

        // Expand the window
        for (int high = 0; high < nums.length; high++) {

            // Add current element
            windowSum += nums[high];

            // Window size becomes k
            if (high - low + 1 == k) {

                // Update answer using current window
                maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, windowSum);

                // Slide the window
                windowSum -= nums[low];
                low++;
            }
        }

        // Convert maximum sum into average
        return (double) maxSum / k;
    }
}
